  text:
  - "<b><color=#FFD700>Police Training Manual \u2013 Firearm Handling</color></b>\r\nIssued
    to all Police Recruits\n\r\n<b>Section 1: <color=#FFD700>Equipping your firearm</color></b>\r\nTo
    ensure proper firearm operation, follow the steps below when equipping your issued
    firearm:\r\n\n1 - <color=#FFD700>Revolver \u2013 Press 1 to equip</color>.\r\n\r\n2
    - <color=#FFD700>Check your inventory for key binding</color> if you do not know
    how to equip a weapon\n\n3 - If you find an <color=#FFD700>upgrade part</color>
    for your weapon go to the <color=#FFD700>inventory and use it</color> to apply
    that upgrade.\r\r\r\n"
  - "<b>Section 2: <color=#FFD700>Shooting Procedure</color></b>\r\r\n\n1 - <color=#FFD700>Shooting
    \u2013 Press Left Click</color> to shoot your weapon.\r\n\r\n2 - <color=#FFD700>Aiming
    - Press Right Click</color> for a careful and precise shot.\r\n\r\n3 - When out
    of ammunition <color=#FFD700>Press V to melee</color>.\r"
  - "<b>Section 3: <color=#FFD700>Reloading Procedure</color></b>\r\nTo ensure proper
    firearm operation, follow the steps below when reloading your issued sidearm:\r\n\n1
    - <color=#FFD700>Initiate Reloading \u2013 Press R</color> to enter the reloading
    stance.\r\n\r\n2 - <color=#FFD700>Load Ammunition</color> \u2013 While in this
    stance, <color=#FFD700>press Left Click</color> to insert each round manually.\r\n\r\n3
    - <color=#FFD700>Complete Reloading</color> \u2013 Once the weapon is loaded,
    <color=#FFD700>press R again</color> to return the weapon to active duty.\r\n\r\nNote:
    Officers are required to practice this procedure until it becomes second nature.
    Proper reloading under pressure may determine survival in the field.\r\n"
